children.subject: You might want to look into transferring the CC credit to Berkeley and taking CS 47B instead; that may make your schedule more manageable.

history.content: Talk to your advisor. If you transfer from a CCC, assit.org should be able to tell you whether you have equivalent credit for cs61b so you can skip it completely or take cs 47b. If you transfer from a non-CCC, all your CS courses at your old school needs to get manually evaluated for equivalency with UCB CS credits. You're still likely to only have to take cs47b.

Hi,

I am an incoming transfer student (junior). I consider taking CS 61A, CS 61B, and EECS 16A during the fall semester. I understand that taking 61A and 61B concurrently is not ideal, but I have taken a data structures course in Java at my community college and did well. I also have some prior Python experience. Do you think it is possible to take these CS 61A, CS 61B, and EECS 16A and make the most of them, or is it too much load?

Additional reasons:

- having only 5 semesters to graduate, I'm trying to complete all required lower divisions (6 courses) during my first 2 semsters

- I have completed most of the other requirements at my community college, except AC and Ethics requirements

Thank you!
history.subject: Taking CS 61A and 61B concurrently
